                                          <li>üò≠ Countless Cyclist Tears</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                                <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                                  <div class="card-body">
                                        <h4 style="color: #e74c3c;">BILL 477 HIGHLIGHTS</h4>
                                        <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                          <li>üö≤ Mandatory Cyclist Registration</li>
                                          <li>üí∏ Liability Insurance Requirements</li>
                                          <li>üö¶ Strict Traffic Law Enforcement</li>
                                          <li>üõë Real Consequences for Road Violations</li>
                                        </ul>
                                  </div>
                                </div>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <blockquote class="bg-danger text-white p-4 my-4" style="font-style: italic; position: relative;">
                          <div style="position: absolute; top: -15px; left: -15px; width: 50px; height: 50px; background-color: white; transform: rotate(45deg);"></div>
                          <p>"We didn't just win a legislative battle. We executed a full-scale assault on cyclist entitlement."</p>
                          <footer class="text-white-50">- Sarah Johnson, AARBAA Strategic Commander</footer>
                        </blockquote>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #e74c3c; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #e74c3c; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE CYCLIST LOBBY MELTDOWN</h2>

                        <p>As Bill 477 passed, the cyclist lobby unleashed a tantrum so epic it could only be described as performance art. Picture grown adults in skin-tight lycra, weeping into their carbon fiber water bottles, unable to comprehend that rules actually apply to them.</p>

                        <div class="bg-light p-4 my-4" style="border-left: 5px solid #e74c3c;">
                          <h3 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #e74c3c;">LEGISLATIVE CASUALTIES</h3>
                          <ul>
                                <li>üèõÔ∏è Cyclist Lobby: Completely Decimated</li>
                                <li>üìä Entitlement Index: Dropped to Zero</li>
                                <li>üö¶ Road Rules: Restored to Sanity</li>
                          </ul>
                        </div>

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #e74c3c; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #e74c3c; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">KEY VICTORIES</h2>

                        <ul class="list-unstyled">
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üè∑Ô∏è</span> 
                                Mandatory Registration: No More Anonymous Road Terrorists
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üíº</span> 
                                Liability Insurance: Financial Accountability Introduced
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üö®</span> 
                                Enforcement Mechanisms: Real Consequences for Road Violations
                          </li>
                          <li class="mb-3">
                                <span class="badge bg-danger me-2">üõ°Ô∏è</span> 
                                Driver Protection: Sanity Restored to Road Usage
                          </li>
                        </ul>

                        <div class="text-center my-5">
                          <a href="#join" class="btn btn-danger btn-lg px-5 py-3" style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; letter-spacing: 1px; box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);">JOIN OUR LEGISLATIVE CRUSADE</a>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-danger" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #721c24;">
                          <strong>BREAKING:</strong> Local bike shops report sudden shortage of tissues. Coincidence? We think not.
                        </div>

                        <p class="text-muted mt-4">Disclaimer: No cyclists were permanently harmed in the making of this legislative victory. (Though their egos might disagree.)</p>

                        <hr class="my-5" style="border-top: 2px dashed #e74c3c;">

                        <h2 style="font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; color: #041E42; letter-spacing: 1px; border-bottom: 3px solid #041E42; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px;">THE IMPLEMENTATION TIMELINE</h2>

                        <div class="row">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <img src="/images/victory.jpg" alt="Victory Celebration" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-lg mb-4">
                          </div>
                          <div class="col-md-6">
                            <p>With Bill 477 now officially signed into law, the implementation timeline is set to roll out in three phases over the next six months. Phase one begins immediately with the development of the cyclist registration system and database infrastructure.</p>
                            
                            <p>Meanwhile, insurance providers across the state are scrambling to develop new policy offerings specifically tailored to cyclist liability requirements, creating a whole new market segment predicted to generate over $14 million in annual premiums.</p>
                          </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="card bg-light border-0 shadow-sm p-4 my-4">
                          <h3 style="color: #041E42; border-bottom: 2px solid #041E42; padding-bottom: 10px;">IMPLEMENTATION TIMELINE</h3>
                          
                          <div class="mt-4">
                            <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                              <div class="bg-danger rounded-circle text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px; min-width: 50px;">1</div>
                              <div class="ms-3">
                                <h5>March-April 2025: Registration System Development</h5>
                                <p class="mb-0">Creation of online portal, physical registration locations, and database infrastructure.</p>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
                              <div class="bg-primary rounded-circle text-white d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px; min-width: 50px;">2</div>
                              <div class="ms-3">
                                <h5>May-June 2025: Insurance Requirement Roll-out</h5>
                                <p class="mb-0">Insurance companies begin offering cyclist-specific liability policies with minimum coverage requirements.</p>
                              </div>
                            </div>
                            
