                        <div class="table-responsive">
                          <table class="table table-striped table-hover">
                            <thead class="table-dark">
                              <tr>
                                <th>Revenue Source</th>
                                <th>Year 1 Projection</th>
                                <th>5-Year Projection</th>
                              </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                              <tr>
                                <td>Registration Fees</td>
                                <td>$7.2 million</td>
                                <td>$42.3 million</td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr>
                                <td>Violation Penalties</td>
                                <td>$4.5 million</td>
                                <td>$27.8 million</td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr>
                                <td>Administrative Fees</td>
                                <td>$1.8 million</td>
                                <td>$10.5 million</td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class="table-primary">
                                <td><strong>Total State Revenue</strong></td>
                                <td><strong>$13.5 million</strong></td>
                                <td><strong>$80.6 million</strong></td>
                              </tr>
                            </tbody>
                          </table>
                        </div>

                        <div class="alert alert-primary mt-4" role="alert" style="border-left: 5px solid #0A3161;">
                          <strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong> Our legislative team is already drafting follow-up legislation (Bill 478) which will establish dedicated cyclist lanes that are physically separated from vehicle traffic, funded entirely by the new cyclist registration and penalty fees. This represents the ultimate AARBAA vision: separate paths for separate uses.
                        </div>

                        <div class="row mt-5">
                          <div class="col-md-6">
